From March 17, 2020 until March 31 2020 in France, the Prime Minister has implemented a nationwide lockdown. Movement outside of the home is prohibited except for the following reasons: 
(1) Journeys between home and the place or places of exercise of professional activity and business trips that cannot be postponed;
(2) Travel to purchase supplies necessary for professional activity and purchases of basic necessities in establishments whose activities remain authorized;
(3) Travel for health reasons;
(4) Travel for compelling family reasons, for the assistance of vulnerable people or for childcare;
(5) Short trips, close to home, related to the individual physical activity of people, the exclusion of any collective sporting activity, and the needs of pets. 
Local government officials may further restrict movement if local conditions require.People traveling outside of the home for these exceptions must bring documentation justifying that their movements fall within the scope of these exceptions.

