 UPDATE: The original policy was mandatory (unspecified/implied). On March 17, 2020, the French Ministry of Justice announced that violation of limits on moving outside one's home, failure to bring documentation justifying an authorized trip, and violation of additional local restrictions where applicable are now punished with a fine of 135 euros on a first offense and 375 euros on the second offense.

